column3: Definition
AL obo:IAO_0000115@en
Dataset created for the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project that contains data about observations of pathological conditions in one specimen.
Section of a paleopathology dataset created for the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project containing data about one pathological lesion.
column5: There are several types of paleopathology dataset sections designed for specific types of observation.

column3: Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of added bone.
Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of bone loss.
Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of osteoarthritis and/or osteoporosis.
Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of skeletal trauma.
A dataset containing data about an anatomical region of interest and its usage in a certain research context.

column2: Phaleron anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying aspect, anatomical site and extent of involvement for one anatomical region of interest that is part of an osteological observation.

column2: Phaleron anatomcial region of interest aspect specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying the anatomical aspect of an anatomical region of interest that is part of an osteological observation.
A textual entity that is about a set of pathological observations.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the skull.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the vertebral column.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the thorax.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the os coxae.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the shoulder girdle.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the upper limbs.
A textual entity that is about pathological observations on the lower limbs.

column2: Mixed cranial bone formation and loss dataset section
column3: Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of mixed bone formation and loss in the skull.

column2: Mixed postcranial bone formation and loss dataset section
column3: Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of mixed bone formation and loss in the postcranium.

column2: Phaleron mixed bone formation and loss anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying anatomical aspect and extent of involvement for various features that are part of an observation of mixed bone formation and loss.
Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of vertebral pathology.

column2: Skull size and shape dataset section
column3: Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of abnormal size and/or shape in a skull.

column2: Long bone size and shape dataset section
column3: Section of a paleopathology dataset containing data about one observation of abnormal size and/or shape in a long bone.

column2: Phaleron skull anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying a set of anatomical regions of interest on a skull as defined by the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project.

column2: Phaleron long bone anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying a set of anatomical regions of interest on a long bone as used by the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project.

column2: Phaleron left femur anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying a set of anatomical regions of interest on the left femur as used by the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project.

column2: Phaleron right femur anatomical region of interest specification
column3: An anatomical region of interest specification specifying a set of anatomical regions of interest on the right femur as used by the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project.
